# Backend Instructions

- Keep controllers, handlers, or tools thin; push business logic into services.
- Use structured error handling with clear user-safe messages and actionable logs.
- Prefer existing logging patterns and include identifiers that help trace requests.
- Use `async`/`await` consistently; avoid mixed promise styles without reason.
- Avoid unnecessary new dependencies when the standard library or repo utilities already cover the need.
- Preserve API contracts and serialization formats unless the change explicitly includes a migration plan.
